ndian home interior style is one that boasts intricacy, details and fine patterns. This kind of interior style grabs the attention to a certain focal point and is wise for larger homes. Whilst a minimalist home works on a clean slate and does not include intricate details and patterns. It\u2019s subtle to the eye and allows for a free flow of thoughts. This kind of interior design style is perfect for compact apartments and small homes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Bulky v\/s sleek: <\/strong>Bulky furniture can be a large armchair, a tufted headboard, a display furniture that\u2019s protruding out of the walls or simply a giant table that fits all your accessories. Bulky can often create the illusion of clutter and is best avoided for compact apartments. Sleek designs and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-pantry-storage\/\">modular storage solutions<\/a>, however, bring a sense of functionality and aesthetics to the space, making it a fine choice amongst homeowners.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Vibrant v\/s neutral: <\/strong>Depending on your style and needs, you can choose between a vibrant popping home or a neutral muted hue home. A vibrant home resembles a colourful boho vibe and is a playful, cheery palate whilst a neutral muted hued home offers a tranquil, comforting experience and is often synonymous with peaceful, meditative palates.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class='white' style='background:rgba(0,0,0,0); border:solid 0px rgba(0,0,0,0); border-radius:0px; padding:0px 0px 0px 0px;'>\n<div id='slider_36177' class='owl-carousel sa_owl_theme owl-pagination-true autohide-arrows' data-slider-id='slider_36177' style='visibility:hidden;'>\n<div id='slider_36177_slide01' class='sa_hover_container' style='padding:0% 0%; margin:0px 0%; background-image:url(&quot;https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/20200651\/seeking-the-right-interior-design-inspiration-interior-design-basic-knowledge.jpg&quot;); background-position: